 : Finset S → ι),\n    37→    ∃ (i : ι) (H : Set S),\n    38→      Cardinal.mk H ≥ targets i ∧\n    39→      ∀ s : Finset S, s.card = r → (↑s : Set S) ⊆ H → c s = i\n    40→\n    41→/-- **Erdős Problem 1167** (Erdős–Hajnal–Rado):\n    42→    For $r \\geq 2$ and $\\lambda$ infinite, does\n    43→    $2^\\lambda \\to (\\kappa_\\alpha + 1)^{r+1}$ imply $\\lambda \\to (\\kappa_\\alpha)^r$? -/\n    44→@[category research open, AMS 3 5]\n    45→theorem erdos_1167 : answer(sorry) ↔\n    46→    ∀ {ι : Type*} (κ : ι → Cardinal) (lam : Cardinal) (r : ℕ),\n    47→      r ≥ 2 → ℵ₀ ≤ lam →\n    48→      CardinalPartitionRel ((2 : Cardinal) ^ lam) (fun α => κ α + 1) (r + 1) →\n    49→      CardinalPartitionRel lam κ r := by\n    50→  sorry\n    51→\n    52→end Erdos1167\n    53→"}]},"uuid":"e211c550-8a9c-48d1-a162-fdf9aa0d30ce","timestamp":"2026-03-11T15:34:49.645Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"a6476fe2-f7b3-4a9b-8b19-63c5c9d601bd"}
